[2026-04-08T21:45:24.864Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01B24bGzbWozuAkJerWXmjz8","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me compile the complete report.\n\n---\n\n## Complete Codebase Exploration Report: auto-invoicer\n\n### Project Overview\n\n**InvoiceFlow** (auto-invoicer) is a next-generation invoice management platform designed for freelancers, micro-businesses, and accountants. The project leverages AI-powered OCR extraction, multi-country compliance features, and dynamic theming for invoice generation. Currently in early development with a functional themed invoice form UI.\n\n**Business Domain**: Invoice Management & Automation\n\n---\n\n### Directory Structure\n\n```\nauto-invoicer/\n├── .claude/                          # Claude Code workspace configuration\n│   ├── brand-manual.md\n│   ├── CLAUDE.md                     # Project documentation (tech stack, conventions)\n│   ├── commands/\n│   │   ├── scan-contexts.md\n│   │   └── structure-rules.md\n│   ├── logs/                         # Claude execution logs\n│   ├── settings.json                 # Workspace settings\n│   ├── settings.local.json\n│   └── skills/                       # Claude skills (brain-training, codebase-init, etc.)\n├── .github/\n│   └── workflows/\n│       └── ci.yml                    # GitHub Actions CI/CD configuration\n├── .gitignore                        # Git ignore patterns\n├── public/                           # Static assets (SVGs)\n│   ├── file.svg\n│   ├── globe.svg\n│   ├── next.svg\n│   ├── vercel.svg\n│   └── window.svg\n├── src/                              # Source code\n│   ├── app/                          # Next.js App Router pages\n│   │   ├── favicon.ico\n│   │   ├── globals.css               # Tailwind CSS + CSS custom properties\n│   │   ├── layout.tsx                # Root layout with font imports\n│   │   └── page.tsx                  # Main invoice form page\n│   └── components/                   # Reusable React components\n│       └── invoice/                  # Invoice-specific components\n│           ├── InvoiceForm.tsx       # Main form component (client-side)\n│           ├── ThemeContext.tsx      # Theme state context provider\n│           ├── ThemeSwitcher.tsx     # Theme switcher UI component\n│           └── theme.ts              # Theme token definitions\n├── requirements/\n│   └── solution.md                   # Complete solution design document (13.8KB)\n├── .gitignore\n├── eslint.config.mjs                 # ESLint flat config\n├── next.config.ts                    # Next.js configuration\n├── next-env.d.ts                     # Auto-generated Next.js types\n├── package.json                      # Project dependencies & scripts\n├── package-lock.json                 # Locked dependency versions\n├── postcss.config.mjs                # PostCSS configuration (Tailwind v4)\n├── tsconfig.json                     # TypeScript configuration\n└── README.md                          # Next.js default README\n```\n\n---\n\n### Complete File Listing with Descriptions\n\n#### Configuration & Meta Files\n\n| File | Purpose | Domain |\n|------|---------|--------|\n| **package.json** | npm scripts, dependencies (Next.js 16, React 19, Tailwind v4) | Build Configuration |\n| **tsconfig.json** | TypeScript compiler options, path aliases (`@/*` → `src/*`) | Build Configuration |\n| **next.config.ts** | Next.js build configuration (currently empty stub) | Build Configuration |\n| **eslint.config.mjs** | ESLint flat config with next/core-web-vitals and TypeScript rules | Code Quality |\n| **postcss.config.mjs** | PostCSS plugins for Tailwind CSS v4 | Styling |\n| **.gitignore** | Version control ignores (node_modules, .next, .env files) | Version Control |\n| **next-env.d.ts** | Auto-generated Next.js type definitions | Build Artifact |\n\n#### CI/CD & DevOps\n\n| File | Purpose | Domain |\n|------|---------|--------|\n| **.github/workflows/ci.yml** | GitHub Actions CI pipeline: lint, build on push/PR to master | CI/CD |\n| **.claude/settings.json** | Claude Code workspace metadata (project name, timestamps) | IDE Configuration |\n\n#### Claude Code Resources\n\n| File | Purpose | Domain |\n|------|---------|--------|\n| **.claude/CLAUDE.md** | Complete tech stack documentation, conventions, architecture overview | Documentation |\n| **.claude/brand-manual.md** | Brand guidelines (referenced but not detailed) | Branding |\n| **.claude/commands/structure-rules.md** | Next.js 15+ App Router structural conventions | Guidelines |\n| **.claude/commands/scan-contexts.md** | Context scanning procedures (referenced) | Documentation |\n| **.claude/skills/** | Custom Claude Code skills (brain training, codebase init, context mapping) | IDE Tools |\n\n#### Source Code - App Layer\n\n| File | Purpose | Business Domain |\n|------|---------|-----------------|\n| **src/app/layout.tsx** | Root layout wrapper; imports Geist/Geist_Mono/Caveat fonts from next/font/google; renders children | Web Framework |\n| **src/app/page.tsx** | Main page component; client-side (`\"use client\"`); provides theme context; renders ThemeSwitcher + InvoiceForm | Invoice UI |\n| **src/app/globals.css** | Global Tailwind CSS imports + CSS custom properties for light/dark modes; base colors | Styling |\n| **src/app/favicon.ico** | Favicon asset | Web Framework |\n\n#### Source Code - Components\n\n| File | Purpose | Business Domain |\n|------|---------|-----------------|\n| **src/components/invoice/InvoiceForm.tsx** | Main invoice form component (310 lines); displays invoice header, dates, supplier/customer fields, line items table, totals summary, action buttons; theme-aware with dynamic Tailwind classes | Invoice Creation |\n| **src/components/invoice/theme.ts** | Theme token system with two theme presets: `minimal-mono` (ultra-minimal monochrome) and `paper-perfect` (warm paper aesthetic); defines 60+ CSS token properties per theme | Theme System |\n| **src/components/invoice/ThemeContext.tsx** | React Context for theme state management; provides `theme` object and `setTheme` function; default theme is `paper-perfect` | State Management |\n| **src/components/invoice/ThemeSwitcher.tsx** | Fixed header component with theme toggle buttons; allows switching between the two themes | Theme UI |\n\n#### Static Assets\n\n| File | Purpose | Domain |\n|------|---------|--------|\n| **public/file.svg, globe.svg, next.svg, vercel.svg, window.svg** | Boilerplate Next.js placeholder SVG icons | Assets |\n\n#### Requirements & Documentation\n\n| File | Purpose | Domain |\n|------|---------|--------|\n| **requirements/solution.md** | Comprehensive solution design document (13.8KB); includes executive summary, system architecture diagrams, technology stack (Supabase, Groq, React-PDF, RevenueCat), complete PostgreSQL schema with ERD, internationalization (i18n) strategy, country-specific invoice rules, API design, security & compliance, deployment guidelines | Project Specification |\n| **README.md** | Default Next.js boilerplate README | Documentation |\n\n---\n\n### Technology Stack\n\n| Layer | Technology | Version | Purpose |\n|-------|-----------|---------|---------|\n| **Framework** | Next.js | 16.0.6 | App Router, SSR, edge runtime |\n| **React** | React | 19.2.0 | UI component library |\n| **Language** | TypeScript | 5 | Type safety |\n| **Styling** | Tailwind CSS | v4 | Utility-first CSS with PostCSS plugin |\n| **Fonts** | next/font/google | — | Geist Sans, Geist Mono, Caveat (handwriting) |\n| **Linting** | ESLint | 9 | Code quality checks |\n| **Build Tool** | Next.js (built-in) | — | Webpack-based bundling |\n\n**Planned Integrations** (per solution.md):\n- **Supabase**: PostgreSQL DB, auth, storage, realtime\n- **Groq AI**: LLaVA/Mixtral for OCR and LLM processing\n- **React-PDF**: PDF generation\n- **RevenueCat**: Subscription management\n- **next-intl**: Internationalization\n- **Radix UI**: Accessible component primitives\n- **Zustand + TanStack Query**: State & data caching\n- **Zod**: Runtime validation\n- **Lucide React**: Icon library\n- **date-fns**: Date utilities\n- **react-dropzone**: File uploads\n- **framer-motion**: Animations\n\n---\n\n### Key Business Features (from Code & Design Document)\n\n#### Current Implementation\n- **Multi-theme Invoice Form**: Two distinct visual themes (minimal-mono, paper-perfect)\n- **Dynamic Form Fields**: Dates, supplier/customer info, line items, totals\n- **Theme-Aware Styling**: Context-driven theming system with token-based design\n- **Responsive Layout**: Max-width container with Tailwind utilities\n\n#### Planned Features (requirements/solution.md)\n- **AI-Powered OCR**: Extract invoice data from images using Groq vision models\n- **Multi-Country Support**: CZ, DE, UK with country-specific validation rules\n- **Invoice Management**: CRUD operations (issued, received, proforma, credit notes)\n- **PDF/CSV/XML Export**: Multiple output formats\n- **Subscription Management**: RevenueCat integration for freemium model\n- **Contact Management (CRM)**: Supplier/customer database\n- **Dashboard & Analytics**: Invoice overview widgets\n- **Team Collaboration**: Multi-user organizations with role-based access\n- **Internationalization (i18n)**: Support for multiple languages via next-intl\n- **Real-time Sync**: Supabase realtime features\n- **PWA Support**: Offline capability with local caching\n\n---\n\n### Database Schema (Planned - from solution.md)\n\nCore entities:\n- **users** - Extended Supabase auth.users\n- **organizations** - Business entities with country, tax IDs, entity type\n- **team_members** - Organization membership with role-based access\n- **contacts** - Customer/supplier CRM\n- **invoices** - Invoice documents with full audit trail\n- **invoice_items** - Line item details\n- **attachments** - File storage references\n- **subscriptions** - RevenueCat integration\n- **country_configs** - Seeded country rules (VAT rates, formats, validation)\n\n---\n\n### Code Patterns & Conventions\n\n**Naming**\n- Components: PascalCase (`InvoiceForm`, `ThemeSwitcher`)\n- Files: kebab-case (configs), PascalCase (components)\n- Variables: camelCase\n- Theme tokens: camelCase\n\n**Patterns**\n- **Theming**: Token-based system using React Context with Tailwind class strings\n- **Styling**: Tailwind v4 with `@import \"tailwindcss\"` syntax (NOT v3 directives)\n- **State**: React `useState` + Context API (no Redux/Zustand yet)\n- **Imports**: Absolute path alias `@/*` → `./src/*`\n- **Client Components**: Explicit `\"use client\"` directive for interactive components\n\n---\n\n### Development Workflow\n\n**Scripts** (package.json)\n```bash\nnpm run dev      # Start Next.js dev server on localhost:3000\nnpm run build    # Production build\nnpm run start    # Run production build\nnpm run lint     # ESLint validation\n```\n\n**CI/CD** (GitHub Actions)\n- Trigger: push to master branch or PR to master\n- Steps: npm ci → npm run lint → npm run build\n\n---\n\n### Project Status & Dependencies\n\n**Stage**: Early Development (Alpha)\n- Core UI infrastructure complete\n- Theme system functional\n- Form layout designed but not wired to backend\n- No backend integrations yet (Supabase, Groq, RevenueCat planned)\n\n**Dependencies**: \n- 3 production deps (next, react, react-dom)\n- 5 devDeps (Tailwind, TypeScript, ESLint, types)\n- Total: ~8 direct dependencies (minimal footprint)\n\n**Node Version**: 20+ (per CI configuration)\n\n---\n\n### Important Notes\n\n1. **Tailwind v4 Syntax**: Uses `@import \"tailwindcss\"` + `@theme inline {}` (not v3's `@tailwind` directives)\n2. **No Backend Yet**: All backend APIs defined in solution.md but not implemented\n3. **Theming is Central**: The entire invoice UI is theme-driven; design changes must account for token system\n4. **Type Safety**: Full TypeScript strict mode enabled\n5. **AI Integration Planned**: Groq LLM will handle OCR, data extraction, and predictions once integrated\n\n---\n\nThis codebase represents a well-structured, early-stage SaaS application for invoice management with a focus on AI automation, multi-country compliance, and user experience through themeable interfaces. The solution design is comprehensive, and the initial implementation establishes a solid foundation for progressive development of planned features."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3222cf1b-2930-4f4b-a1c0-9f3e8ac0d429","uuid":"35325584-89a9-441c-aa79-ddce0222c2bb","timestamp":"2026-04-08T21:45:24.854Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Thoroughly explore the codebase at C:\\Users\\mkdol\\dolla\\auto-invoicer. I need a complete picture of every file and directory. List all files recursively (excluding node_modules, .next, .git directories). Also read the key files to understand what each one does - especially:\n- All files under src/\n- All config files (next.config.*, tsconfig.json, package.json, etc.)\n- requirements/solution.md\n- Any other source files\n\nFor each file, note what business domain/feature it relates to. Report the full list of files with brief descriptions.","agentId":"ad52a4750deb79e20","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me compile the complete report.\n\n---\n\n## Complete Codebase Exploration Report: auto-invoicer\n\n### Project Overview\n\n**InvoiceFlow** (auto-invoicer) is a next-generation invoice management platform designed for freelancers, micro-businesses, and accountants. The project leverages AI-powered OCR extraction, multi-country compliance features, and dynamic theming for invoice generation. Currently in early development with a functional themed invoice form UI.\n\n**Business Domain**: Invoice Management & Automation\n\n---\n\n### Directory Structure\n\n```\nauto-invoicer/\n├── .claude/                          # C